        <abstract> 
<p>Thinks AG’s review [of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>] will aid much in making people think about subject.</p>  
<p>Has been savagely and unfairly reviewed by Adam Sedgwick in the <hi rend="italic">Spectator</hi> [24 Mar 1860],</p>  
<p>but thinks F. J. Pictet’s review in opposition ["Sur l’origine de l’espèce", <hi rend="italic">Arch. Sci. Phys. &amp; Nat.</hi> n.s. 7 (1860): 231–55] a very fair one.</p> 
        </abstract>
